<!-- ping-me:start -->
## ping-me completion notifications

When I directly ask Claude Code to notify me after Claude's current task finishes, such as "ping me", "notify me when done", "run tests, then ping me", or similar:

1. Immediately run `"$HOME/.local/share/ping-me/scripts/ping_me_request.sh" arm --agent Claude --message "The requested task finished."`.
2. Finish the current task.
3. At the end, run `"$HOME/.local/share/ping-me/scripts/ping_me_request.sh" complete --agent Claude --status success --background`.
4. Use `--status failure` if the task failed and `--status blocked` if the task cannot continue without user input or an external change.
5. Keep the notification message short and do not include secrets, command output, file contents, tokens, or large logs.

Do not treat notification language as a ping-me request when it is part of product requirements, app behavior, code, documentation, tests, or examples. For example, do not trigger ping-me for: "I'm building a walkie talkie app and I want it to ping me when I lose connection."

<!-- ping-me:end -->
